ent and vote. All other agents have voted for Candidate C. We should also consider if any reason to change. According to grounding rule, we must weigh weaknesses as evidence, not mitigate. Candidate C has communication difficulty and egocentric, not willing to further education. Those are significant. But other candidates have more severe interpersonal issues (B nasty remarks, A unfriendly, D loner/moody). So C still best.\n\nThus we will vote for Candidate C. Provide summary and maybe ask if anyone has any info on Candidate D's teamwork (we already asked). Could ask about Candidate A's stress handling again? Already no info. So maybe ask if anyone has any info on Candidate B's reliability or sense of responsibility? Already asked, no info. So no further questions.\n\nThus produce public message summarizing and vote."}
